&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Breast Screening Nurse - Breast Imaging Unit &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the Beds and Herts Breast Screening Programme as a Breast Screening Nurse. The service is one of the biggest breast screening services in England with up to 185 women being assessed each month. The role sits within a well-established Breast Screening nursing team supporting women through the assessment process and working closely with the multidisciplinary team existing of Consultant Radiologists, Breast Clinicians, a Consultant Radiographer and a Consultant Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to deliver clinical excellence within the Breast Screening Service and in the future assist in the development of initiatives to support increasing the uptake of screening. This will require candidates to have either successfully completed a specialist post registration breast cancer care course or be prepared to do so on commencement of the role, as well as have a demonstrable knowledge of breast cancer diagnosis and treatment. We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and innovative individual who is willing to learn and work within a changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 - 37.5 hrs per week or part-time would be considered &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Christine Khan, Breast Screening Nurse – 01582 497594&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Dixon - Consultant Nurse - amanda.dixon@ldh.nhs.uk  01582 497594&lt;/p&gt;
